Reasoning: The paper deals with problems related to graph theory, specifically identifying codes, (open) locating-dominating sets, and metric dimension on interval and permutation graphs. These topics are closely related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of these problems, which falls under computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves graph theory and combinatorics (cs.GT) and computational geometry (cs.CG) in the context of interval graphs.
